Deputy National Security Advisor for Strategic Communications, Ben Rhodes, met with Bishops Mar Awa Royel and Mar Paulus Benjamin of the Assyrian Church of the East. The Bishops discussed the challenges faced by Christian communities in Syria and Iraq, as well as the recent attacks by ISIL on Assyrian Christian villages along the Khabur River in northeastern Syria. Rhodes strongly condemned ISIL's targeting of vulnerable religious populations in the Middle East and outlined the steps the Administration has taken to protect and support those impacted by ISIL's terror. He also reaffirmed the Administration's commitment to support the Assyrian Christian community and to degrade and defeat ISIL.